==English==
===Noun===
'''arithmetic mean'''

#(''mathematics'') The [[measure of central tendency]] of a set of values computed by dividing the sum of the values by their number; commonly called the '''mean''' or the '''average'''.
#:''The arithmetic mean of 3, 6, 2, 3 and 6 is (3 + 6 + 2 + 3 + 6) / 5 = 4''

====Usage note====
*In scientific and economic contexts, this term is preferable to ''average'', which can also mean the [[mode]] or the [[median]] depending on context.

